Definition: the phenomenon of a popular trend attracting even greater popularity
Example: in periods of high merger activity there is a bandwagon effect with more and more firms seeking to engage in takeover activity; polls are accused of creating a bandwagon effect to benefit their candidate
Synonyms: consequence, the, phenomenon, of, a, popular, trend, attracting, even, greater, popularity, in, periods, high, merger, activity, there, is, bandwagon, effect, with, more, and, firms, seeking, to, engage, takeover, polls, are, accused, creating, benefit, their, candidate
Category: noun.phenomenon
